Im having an issue and trying to asyncly load a component inside the Router component and getting the following error:

`[Vue warn]: Failed to resolve async component: ()=>t.e(0).then(t.bind(null,138))
Reason: Error: Loading chunk 0 failed.`

Route config:
```javascript
export default new Router({
  routes: [
    {
      path: "/",
      name: "HomePage",
      component: HomePage
    }
  ]
});
```
HomePage.vue:

```javascript
import WhyChooseUs from "./WhyChooseUs";
  const BelowFold = () => import(/* webpackChunkName: "below-fold" */ './BelowFold.vue'); // eslint-disable-line

  export default {
    name: "HomePage",
    components: {
      WhyChooseUs,
      BelowFold
    }
  };
```

Webpack Output:
```javascript 
output: {
    path: `${root}/public/assets/`,
    publicPath: "/lead/assets",
    filename: `${fileName()}.js`,
    chunkFilename: "[name].[chunkhash].js"
  }
```

Im only trying to lazy load the components that are in the BelowFold Components.  The code splitting is working as I can see the `below-fold.b0787f8e6be34fdd3141.js` in my assets folder and in the server. But in the error it says error loading chunk 0 instead of below-fold?
